Seer or Reviver - Mention anything about poem.
Mason Leader - Make a greeting or entrance starting with H. (Hello, Hi, Howdy, Here I am, etc.)
Stalker or Harlot - Make a greeting or entrance relating to the time of your appearance. (Morning, Good day, Evening, etc.)
Gravedigger - Show empathy to the last night's death. (Poor Amanita, RIP, etc.)
Protector or Huntsman - Make your first sentence of the day a question instead of affirmative sentence.
Messiah, Militia, Vanilla variation, Zealot, any other Village alignment - Make your first sentence of the day a negative sentence.

Witch or Shaman - Include at least one emoji in your first sentence of the day. This will take over all codes above's priority. (For example, if you mention about poem with emoji, it means you saw a Witch or a Shaman.)
Alchemist - Make a sentence that includes the article a or an, and misuse it on purpose, as the first sentence of the day. (For example, I suspect an person.)
Puppet or Puppet Master - End the first sentence of the day with four dots if it's Puppet, five dots if it's Master.
Djinn or Succubus - Ask about the existence of Moderator texts at the end of each day and night as if you never knew about its existence before.
Harpy or any other Coven alignment - Mention any avatar's name that is NOT dead or wolves in your first sentence of the day.
